parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of engine mounts can cause excessive engine movement, leading to premature wear on other components, noise, and vibration, which can affect vehicle performance and safety.
An engine fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a total loss, and poses a risk to the safety of the occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: no warning signs or indications of overheating or maintenance needs.
